    <h2>Method</h2>

    <ol>
        <li>In a food processor, pulse the {{ tooltipAmount('coriander', 80, 'g') }}, {{ tooltipAmount('parsley', 30, 'g') }} and {{ tooltipAmount('spinach', 600, 'g') }} in batches, until finely chopped (or do so by hand), then scrape into a bowl.</li>

        <li>Put {{ controlled(75) }}ml oil in a large, heavy-based pot on a medium heat. Add the onion and fry gently, stirring occasionally, for eight minutes, until soft and golden.</li>

        <li>Add the {{ tooltipAmount('garlic', 5, 'cloves') }}, chilli and spices, and cook, stirring regularly, for six minutes. Turn up the heat to high, add the chopped spinach mix and {{ controlled(3) }} more tablespoons of oil, and cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes, until the spinach turns a dark green, almost grey colour. You want it to catch a bit, but not to burn, so turn down the heat if need be.</li>

        <li>Stir in the {{ tooltipAmount('sugar', 1.5, 'tsp') }}, {{ tooltipAmount('lemon juice', 2, 'tbsp') }}, {{ tooltipAmount('stock', 1, 'l') }} and {{ controlled(2) }} teaspoons of salt, scraping the bottom of the pan with a spatula as you do so. Bring to a rapid simmer, then lower the heat to medium, add the {{ tooltipAmount('potatoes', 500, 'g') }} and cook gently for 25 minutes, until they are soft all the way through. Stir in the {{ tooltipAmount('butter beans', 425, 'g') }} and cook for five minutes, until warmed through.</li>

        <li>Off the heat, stir in the roughly chopped extra coriander, then divide the stew between four bowls. Drizzle over some more oil and serve with the lemon wedges.</li>
    </ol>

